definitions.definition: caused , by natural or unnatural means , to be depressed (lower than the surrounding area) or submerged
examples: The sunken ship lay at a depth of 100 feet

definitions.definition: Seeming to have fallen deeper back into the face due to tiredness, illness, or old age.
examples: She looked old and thin with sunken cheeks and hollow eyes.

main_definition: caused , by natural or unnatural means , to be depressed (lower than the surrounding area) or submerged
secondary_definitions: (of eyes or cheeks) Seeming to have fallen deeper back into the face due to tiredness, illness, or old age.
